{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:second-corinthians.11",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 11 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:1",
      "text": "I wish that you would bear with me in a little foolishness, but indeed you do bear with me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:2",
      "text": "For I am jealous over you with a godly jealousy. For I promised you in marriage to one husband, that I might present you as a pure virgin to Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:3",
      "text": "But I am afraid that somehow, as the serpent deceived Eve in his craftiness, so your minds might be corrupted from the simplicity that is in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:4",
      "text": "For if he who comes preaches another Jesus whom we didn’t preach, or if you receive a different spirit which you didn’t receive, or a different “good news” which you didn’t accept, you put up with that well enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:5",
      "text": "For I reckon that I am not at all behind the very best apostles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:6",
      "text": "But though I am unskilled in speech, yet I am not unskilled in knowledge. No, in every way we have been revealed to you in all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:7",
      "text": "Or did I commit a sin in humbling myself that you might be exalted, because I preached to you God’s Good News free of charge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:8",
      "text": "I robbed other assemblies, taking wages from them that I might serve you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:9",
      "text": "When I was present with you and was in need, I wasn’t a burden on anyone, for the brothers, when they came from Macedonia, supplied the measure of my need. In everything I kept myself from being burdensome to you, and I will continue to do so.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:10",
      "text": "As the truth of Christ is in me, no one will stop me from this boasting in the regions of Achaia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:11",
      "text": "Why? Because I don’t love you? God knows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:12",
      "text": "But what I do, that I will continue to do, that I may cut off opportunity from those who desire an opportunity, that in which they boast, they may be recognized just like us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:13",
      "text": "For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, masquerading as Christ’s apostles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:14",
      "text": "And no wonder, for even Satan masquerades as an angel of light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:15",
      "text": "It is no great thing therefore if his servants also masquerade as servants of righteousness, whose end will be according to their works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:16",
      "text": "I say again, let no one think me foolish. But if so, yet receive me as foolish, that I also may boast a little.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:17",
      "text": "That which I speak, I don’t speak according to the Lord, but as in foolishness, in this confidence of boasting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:18",
      "text": "Seeing that many boast after the flesh, I will also boast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:19",
      "text": "For you bear with the foolish gladly, being wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:20",
      "text": "For you bear with a man if he brings you into bondage, if he devours you, if he takes you captive, if he exalts himself, or if he strikes you on the face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:21",
      "text": "To my shame, I speak as though we had been weak. Yet in whatever way anyone is bold (I speak in foolishness), I am bold also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:22",
      "text": "Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they the offspring of Abraham? So am I.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:23",
      "text": "Are they servants of Christ? (I speak as one beside himself.) I am more so: in labors more abundantly, in prisons more abundantly, in stripes above measure, and in deaths often.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:24",
      "text": "Five times I received forty stripes minus one from the Jews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:25",
      "text": "Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times I suffered shipwreck. I have been a night and a day in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:26",
      "text": "I have been in travels often, perils of rivers, perils of robbers, perils from my countrymen, perils from the Gentiles, perils in the city, perils in the wilderness, perils in the sea, perils among false brothers;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:27",
      "text": "in labor and travail, in watchings often, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, and in cold and nakedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:28",
      "text": "Besides those things that are outside, there is that which presses on me daily: anxiety for all the assemblies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:29",
      "text": "Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is caused to stumble, and I don’t burn with indignation?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:30",
      "text": "If I must boast, I will boast of the things that concern my weakness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:31",
      "text": "The God and Father of the Lord Jesus Christ, he who is blessed forever more, knows that I don’t lie.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:32",
      "text": "In Damascus the governor under King Aretas guarded the Damascenes ’ city, desiring to arrest me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.11.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 11:33",
      "text": "I was let down in a basket through a window by the wall, and escaped his hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
